com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast.hints

Enum QueryHintScope

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<QueryHintScope>
      • com.bigdata.rdf.sparql.ast.hints.QueryHintScope
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<QueryHintScope>

    public enum QueryHintScope
extends Enum<QueryHintScope>
    Type safe enumeration for the scope of a query hint. The URI for each scope is plus the name of the enumeration value. For example, http://www.bigdata.com/queryHints#Group would apply to the entire group in which that query hint was found.
    Version:
    $Id$
    Author:
    Bryan Thompson
    See Also:
    QueryHints, ASTQueryHintOptimizer

      • GroupAndSubGroups

        public static final QueryHintScope GroupAndSubGroups
        The group in which the query hint appears and any children of that group. This does not apply to things within ServiceNodes or SubqueryRoots.

      • Prior

        public static final QueryHintScope Prior
        The query hint binds on the previous non-query hint AST node which is not itself a query hint. This may be used to bind a query hint on a StatementPatternNode, a JoinGroupNode, a UnionNode, a ServiceNode, etc. This DOES NOT bind the query hint on the children of that AST node.
